Product description

RIOWOIS Sound Bar for Smart TV

RIOWOIS soundbar delivers an audio experience that is nothing short of extraordinary, with every note and beat coming to life in stunning clarity.

Compact in Size, Strong in Entertainment

Whether you're watching your favorite movies, enjoying your favorite tunes, or engaging in intense gaming sessions, our soundbar elevates the overall entertainment value, delivering crystal-clear dialogue, immersive surround sound, and deep, rich bass.

Three Sound Effects

Three different sound effects are available to enhance your TV viewing experience.

ABS Material+Frosted Finish

ABS material and frosted finishes offer durable and elegant benefits for soundbars. ABS is lightweight and long-lasting, while the frosted finish diffuses light, reduces glare, and minimizes fingerprints, creating a visually appealing and sleek soundbar experience.

More than Just for TV

Sound bar offers multiple connectivity options including AUX, optical, and Bluetooth. It can be easily connected to various streaming devices such as TVs, computers, projectors, cell phones, and tablets, etc.

Twin-magnet Driver

  • Twin-magnet driver provides greater control over the cone movement with improved bass response and overall sound quality.

Remote Control

  • Sound bar is compatible with Fire TV remotes.
  • Additional remotes compatible with Roku box or Roku TVs can be provided as per your request.

Active Subwoofer Compatible

  • Sound bar enhances bass by connecting an active subwoofer.
  • Caution! Soundbar is not compatible with passive subwoofers.

Exclusive Bass Reflex Port

  • Exclusive Bass Reflex Port enhances low-frequency response, producing deeper bass tones with less distortion and noise.

Easily Wall mounted

Package includes all wall mounting kits

Package Included

Output Power 40W
Frequency Response 65Hz – 20KHz
Signal to Noise Ratio 80dB (A-weighting)

      5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Great compact sound bar & easy to set up
      Reviewed in the United States on March 10, 2025
      Size: Without Subwoofer
      Since flatscreen TVs almost always have crappy stock built-in speakers, it’s pretty much a given a soundbar will be needed for decent sound quality. This small-but-mighty and affordable soundbar is the perfect solution for our 32” TV which is mounted on a swing-arm TV... See more
      Since flatscreen TVs almost always have crappy stock built-in speakers, it’s pretty much a given a soundbar will be needed for decent sound quality. This small-but-mighty and affordable soundbar is the perfect solution for our 32” TV which is mounted on a swing-arm TV mount. I simply used heavy-duty Velcro to adhere the soundbar to the bottom of the TV. It actually looks like it was made for the TV.

      I tried using Bluetooth connectivity, but the sound quality wasn’t the best. So, I opted for the optical cable that came with this unit and it sounds great! The soundbar is very durable and was easy to set up.

      The remote is useful to choose how your soundbar is connected and has a few sound options such as Movie, News & Music. Our Fire TV remote turns the soundbar on and off and sometimes they get out os sync but it’s not a huge hassle.

      All-in-all, this compact soundbar fits the bill for us.

      I used to have a soundbar that was bulkier than this one, and had a separate subwoofer. Then I moved and now I have very little space. This one is more compact in size, and works with Bluetooth so it only requires one cord. And it's just the one speaker.

      Prepare yourself for an awe-inspiring journey into the realm of sound! Brace your senses as I unveil the marvel that is this audio system. Let me regale you with a tale of its auditory prowess, commanding bass, and the astounding convenience of its remote control. Oh, and let's not forget about the seamless ease of its setup process. Ah, what a wondrous experience it was!

      Alas, as I embark on recounting my encounter with this masterpiece, I must confess a sorrowful truth that weighs heavily upon my heart: the abominable monster lurking within its Bluetooth connectivity. At first, it was a beacon of hope, radiating flawless wireless connection for a glorious month. Oh, the melodies danced through the air, embracing my ears with sheer delight!

      Yet, like an insidious serpent, a poisonous fog began to creep into this sonic paradise. An odd crackle dared to infiltrate the symphony, faint and negligible at first. Alas, my dear friend, that seemingly harmless crackle grew with malicious intent. It devoured my auditory pleasure, morphing into an uninhibited viral infection that unleashed a relentless barrage of stuttering, loud crackling. Oh, the horror! At this point, it had become nothing short of an abomination, rendering the system utterly useless.

      Fear not, for fortune smiled upon me in the form of a trusty laptop, equipped with a simple yet marvelous headphone jack. Thus, I turned to this faithful companion, reconnecting with the sheer bliss of crystal-clear sound that this system is undeniably capable of producing. Ah, what sweet relief it brought to my distraught soul!

      In conclusion, my dear compatriots of sonic wonder, I implore you to approach this audio system with cautious admiration. Revel in its glorious sound, revel in its powerful bass, and revel in the utter convenience of its dependable remote control. But beware the fickle nature of its Bluetooth connectivity, for it may lead you down a treacherous path of crackling chaos. Should such a misfortune befall you, take solace in the alternative of utilizing a trusty headphone jack, which shall once again restore your auditory nirvana. May your journey through sound be filled with both euphoria and precaution, my friends!

    • Amazon Customer
      4.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      I think it works OK, but with some slight flaws.
      Reviewed in the United States on October 15, 2024
      Size: Without Subwoofer
      The volume is great, and it sounds good in most cases. This works so much better than computer built in speakers, and a lot better than a clip-on speaker made for computers that was supposed to be good according to reviews here. For a small soundbar it has decent... See more
      The volume is great, and it sounds good in most cases. This works so much better than computer built in speakers, and a lot better than a clip-on speaker made for computers that was supposed to be good according to reviews here.

      For a small soundbar it has decent bass and OK stereo imaging. The Bluetooth and the 3.5mm inputs work fine, I haven't had an opportunity to use the subwoofer output so I can't comment on that.

      The remote works OK, but the various tone controls like music, news, and movie don't seem to do much. The remote doesn't come with batteries, and I guess it didn't claim to come with them, but just have a set of AAA ready if you want to use the remote.

      The flaw that I hear is hissing instead of proper sound reproduction at low volumes. It sounds like shh-shh-shhh as people are speaking or music is playing. At first I thought it was my computer soundcard, and I tried multiple soundcards, multiple computer settings and multiple software drivers on my computer. I played with turning the volume on this device up, and the computer volume down and vise-versa. Then I tried it with my phone over Bluetooth, and the same shh-shh-shh effect was there.

      So all I can conclude is it is just that the device is unable to produce usable sound at low volumes, and instead it comes across as noise, scratching or hissing. If you listen at moderate or loud volumes, it probably will be fine. But if you are wanting to listen at low volumes, it can be annoying.
